review_blob: Pours dark orange/brown color with a nice head that gradually dissipated. Fresh hoppy aroma. Nice malty taste and crisp hoppy finish. A well balanced delicious beer.
Pours a hazy copper colour with a compact white head. Taste is incredibly well balanced between the malt, hops and alcohol with a clean bitter finish.
Poured from an imported bottle. Pours a little lighter in colour than the Big Eye IPA. Tropical hops aroma and grapefruit hop taste. A great hoppy IPA.
Poured from a bottle (import). Pours a clear golden colour with slight head. Malty/hoppy aroma. Good balance of malt and hops with a good level of carbonation.
beer_name: Lagunitas A Little Sumpin Sumpin Ale

review_blob: Pours a deep black. A lot going on with the aromas from chocolate, roasted malts, caramel and a big whack of alcohol. Fantastic complex taste to go with the aroma.
Pours dark copper with aromas of pine and grapefruit and white head. Caramel malts lead to a hoppy finish with pine and grapefruit.
Pours classic yellow with thin head. Strong pine hoppy aroma. Nice balance of malts, alcohol and hops. Hard to believe this comes in at 100 IBUs. Very refined and easy to drink.
Dark colour with white head. Aroma is oak and hops. A lot going on with this beer. Initial notes of vanilla and blackcurrant, oak, dark malts and then the hops. Great beer!
Pours classic yellow with a white head. Strong pine hop aroma. Great balance of malts, hops and alcohol. A great Imperial IPA.

Dark amber colour. malty aroma with a hit of hops. Malty flavour with a fair hit of citrous hops at the end and the alcohol well balanced. Smooth on the palate with some bite from the carbonation and a bitter finish.
beer_name: Deschutes Red Chair Northwest Pale Ale

review_blob: Fantastic flavor for a light beer. Deep red in color. Amazing balance of malt and hops. Would be interesting to drink as a full strength beer.

Pours a hazy amber with a decent head that quickly dissipates. Huge hoppy pine aroma. Tastes slightly caramel and then a big whack of pine-resin hops that stays with you. The 7% alcohol is there too and well balanced. A fair amount of carbonation. Overall another great beer from Sixpoint.
